last_episode_to_air.name: Nothing Sudden About It
last_episode_to_air.overview: When an American teenager disappears from a beach party during her senior year trip to Portugal, the Fly Team heads up the search, which is further complicated by the missing teen's parents' differing opinions.

name: FBI: International

next_episode_to_air.name: The Unwinnable War
next_episode_to_air.overview: The deputy inspector general calls on Tate, who is fluent in Spanish, to take on her first undercover field mission, joining Wes and the team in Spain as they investigate a seemingly dirty U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration special agent working out of Madrid.

overview: Follows the elite agents of the FBI's International Fly Team headquartered in Budapest as they travel the world with the mission of protecting Americans wherever they may be.

episodes.name: Pilot (III)
episodes.overview:
Special Agent Scott Forrester and his Budapest-based FBI fly team head to Croatia, after Isobel Castille enlists their help to capture an American fugitive who escaped to Zagreb with a 14-year-old girl. OA continues with the mission overseas, intent on bringing the fugitive to justice, while Europol agent Katrin Jaeger attempts to help the team secure the necessary support and access from the less-than-cooperative local authorities.

The crossover starts on FBI S04E01 All That Glitters (I) and FBI: Most Wanted S03E01 Exposed (II).

episodes.name: The Edge
episodes.overview: The International Fly Team is called on when a young mother flees to Hungary with her son, after losing partial custody of her son in the U.S. However, after the boy is kidnapped from his mother in broad daylight in Budapest, the team questions which parent is the danger in the child’s life

episodes.name: Secrets as Weapons
episodes.overview: The team investigates when the hijacking of millions worth of cryptocurrency en route to a safety vault in Switzerland leaves an American transporter dead and another on the run.

episodes.name: American Optimism
episodes.overview: The team investigates an American citizen who is proclaiming his innocence after seeking sanctuary at Madrid’s U.S. embassy while still covered in the blood of his murdered Spanish boyfriend. Also, Vo and Raines continue to grow their friendship.

episodes.name: The Soul of Chess
episodes.overview: The team investigates an American journalist’s death by poison after his attempt to meet with an anonymous source in Poland. Also, Kellett takes Forrester to task for being overprotective with her during the mission.

episodes.name: The Secrets She Knows
episodes.overview: After a U.S. intelligence negotiator goes missing and her ransacked Paris apartment is discovered to be covered in her blood, the team is on the clock to find her before the country's nuclear secrets fall into the wrong hands. Also, Forrester finds himself drawing certain parallels to his mother's disappearance.

episodes.name: Trying to Grab Smoke
episodes.overview: When an American founder of an illegal adults-only site is killed in Prague, the team is tasked to locate his co-founder, who is still on the run in Czech Republic; Kellett struggles to maintain a relationship with her mother.

episodes.name: Voice of the People
episodes.overview: When a group of Americans are among the victims of a bombing at a festival in Budapest, the team is brought in to find the perpetrators before they strike again. Also, when Vo's new beau is injured in the blast, she re-evaluates what dating truly means while in the bureau.

episodes.name: One Kind of Madman
episodes.overview: The team jets to Bulgaria when terrorists hold hostage for millions in cryptocurrency a concert hall filled with multinational student performers and their families. Raines is intent on proving his field skills, and Forrester receives news of their dog, Tank.

episodes.name: Close to the Sun
episodes.overview: Kellett and the team reluctantly join an investigation in Northern Ireland, when one of Kellett's informants is arrested for his connection to a robbery and murder, and calls her to help clear his name.

episodes.name: Chew Toy
episodes.overview: When an NYPD officer is detained in Transnistria for aggravated assault, the fly team investigates his claims of infiltrating a sex trafficking ring being concealed by those in power; Forrester receives an unusual message from an unknown sender.

episodes.name: One Point One Million Followers
episodes.overview: When a notorious American tech tycoon becomes involved in a murder in Frankfurt, Germany, the team must chase him down amid the local protesters he's incited with his conspiracy theories on social media.

episodes.name: Snakes
episodes.overview: A couple flees to Albania while awaiting sentencing for bilking millions in COVID-19 relief funds from the U.S. government; Kellett works the case from Budapest as she and Forrester try to regain their professional boundaries.

episodes.name: The Kill List
episodes.overview: The team must figure out how to keep the U.S. attorney general safe amid a possible security breach while she's in Hungary for an important meeting.

episodes.name: Shouldn’t Have Left Her
episodes.overview: When Raines' sister goes missing in Kosovo, he goes rogue to find her, putting his job and his life on the line; Kellett and Forrester face further scrutiny from inside the bureau.

episodes.name: Left of Boom
episodes.overview: The Fly Team lands in hot water when Vo is found at the scene where a Hungarian gambling regulator was murdered.

episodes.name: Uprooting
episodes.overview: When an American vintner is shot and killed on his wine estate in France, the team must determine if the region's local protest group with a history of violence against foreigners is to blame.

episodes.name: On These Waters
episodes.overview: Following a frenzied attack by gunmen aboard an American-owned river cruise ship on the Danube, the Fly Team heads to Vienna to investigate why the boat was targeted. Also, Forrester realizes his feelings of mistrust caused by his past are affecting his personal relationships.

episodes.name: Get That Revolution Started
episodes.overview: The Fly Team works to hunt down the sniper responsible for killing an American during an attack targeting a biomedical lab in Belgium. Also, Jaeger clashes with her boss at Europol over her allegiance to the Fly Team.

episodes.name: Black Penguin
episodes.overview: The Fly Team and Jaeger head to Berlin when the 19-year-old son of an American billionaire is found unresponsive in his apartment. As the team works to determine if foul play was involved, they realize there’s a shadowy group on the case as well.

episodes.name: Crestfallen
episodes.overview: When a private jet carrying American citizens is shot down outside of a small town in Poland, the Fly Team looks into the man who missed the flight. Also, Forrester is conflicted when he receives information from his mother.

episodes.name: Unburdened
episodes.overview: The Fly Team and new Europol liaison Megan “Smitty” Garretson investigate when an American police detective on the Federal task force is murdered in Paris while looking into a U.S. company suspected of selling illegal weapons in France and the Middle East.

episodes.name: Don't Say Her Name Again
episodes.overview: When a local predator begins extorting underage American girls online, the team attempts to bring the offender to justice with on-site help from one of the victims; Kellett decides she should find a roommate.

episodes.name: Money Is Meaningless
episodes.overview: The team travels to Mallorca when an American is found brutally murdered on the estate of her powerful father-in-law.

episodes.name: Copper Pots and Daggers
episodes.overview: When a former U.S. Marine is detained in Istanbul on a charge of smuggling antiquities, the Fly Team races against the clock to organize her release before the Turkish police learn the truth behind her visit

episodes.name: Yesterday's Miracle
episodes.overview: The Fly Team searches Bucharest for a Romanian surrogate who goes missing shortly before carrying the biological child of an American couple to term. Also, Forrester’s concern about the safety of his neighbors in Budapest intensifies.

episodes.name: Call It Anarchy
episodes.overview: Vo’s friend from the U.S. Navy calls in a favor to help find her missing nephew in Crete. Meanwhile, Forrester hangs back in Budapest to take care of personal business.

episodes.name: A Proven Liar
episodes.overview: When an American businessman’s bodyguard and girlfriend are kidnapped a few feet away from him in Barcelona, the Fly Team questions if the man is as innocent as he claims. Also, Raines grows closer to Maya, the owner of the team’s favorite local bar.

episodes.name: Hail Mary
episodes.overview: Vo goes under cover when the team investigates the mysterious death of an American model in Milan; Kellett is caught off guard when Dandridge arrives looking for visibility on the case.

episodes.name: Wheelman
episodes.overview: The team races through the streets of Budapest to put a halt to a major art heist about to be perpetrated by an American; Forrester grows angry as Dandridge watches every move the team makes.

episodes.name: BHITW
episodes.overview: When an American basketball player for a Lithuanian team goes into cardiac arrest, the team investigates along with Zoey McKenna, the new agent appointed by Dandridge.

episodes.name: Someone She Knew
episodes.overview: The team races to find a kidnapped American teen in Austria as the clock ticks on Forrester's reassignment.

episodes.name: Glimmers and Ghosts
episodes.overview: The Fly Team and Smitty reunite with Jaeger in Berlin as they all delve into a case involving an unidentified American who killed an elderly German man who appears to have been a covert asset of the ruthless Stasi in East Germany during the Cold War.

episodes.name: Indefensible
episodes.overview: The team investigates the death of an American lawyer working out of Budapest, Hungary, after his is killed by a car bomb; Kellett begins to grow close to Hungarian lieutenant Benedek Erdős as the critical case progresses.

episodes.name: He Who Speaks Dies
episodes.overview: The team and Smitty head to Morocco when a commercial aircraft flying from New York to Athens is grounded and an American citizen on board goes missing; Kellett's relationship with Erdős continues to blossom.

episodes.name: Trust
episodes.overview: The Fly Team lends a helping hand to the Hungarian National Police when one of their police officers is accused of murdering a couple in Budapest; Kellett questions her relationship with Erdős.

episodes.name: Imminent Threat (I)
episodes.overview:
When the abduction of an American architect in Rome appears to be connected to a brewing terror threat in New York City, FBI’s Jubal and Nina join Forrester and his Fly Team in Italy as they work together to find the missing American and shed light on the terrorists’ U.S. target.

The crossover continues on FBI S05E17 Imminent Threat (II) and FBI: Most Wanted S04E16 Imminent Threat (III).

episodes.name: Jealous Mistress
episodes.overview: The Fly Team heads to Vienna to find the culprit of an acid attack on a rising American prima ballerina. Also, Smitty receives some troubling intel from a familiar face.

episodes.name: Blood Feud
episodes.overview: The team jumps into action to protect Forrester when a Russian hit man seeks revenge on him; Raines is sent into a tailspin when someone close to him is taken.

episodes.name: Dead Sprint
episodes.overview: After an American tourist is killed while visiting Stockholm with his girlfriend, the Fly Team must work together to take down a Swedish group responsible for the hate crime.

episodes.name: A Tradition of Secrets
episodes.overview: After a cybersecurity expert robs one of Switzerland's largest and most secretive banks, the Fly Team is called to track down the fugitive. Also, Smitty's loyalty is put to the test.

episodes.name: Fed to the Sharks
episodes.overview: The Fly Team jets off to Portugal when the daughter of a prominent American hotelier becomes the primary suspect in the murder of an employee. Also, Raines becomes concerned about Vo.

episodes.name: Fencing the Mona Lisa
episodes.overview: When a Russian missile is stolen and put on the black market in Budapest, the Fly Team must secure the weapon before a mysterious American arms broker delivers it into the wrong hands.

episodes.name: June
episodes.overview: The Fly Team, with the help of their new intel analyst, Special Agent Amanda Tate, works to clean up the pieces left behind after a massive explosion rocks headquarters and their key suspect slips away.

guest_stars.character: Carjack Victim Used as Human Shield (uncredited)
guest_stars.name: Zsolt Hetyési

episodes.name: The Last Stop
episodes.overview: When an ex-FBI agent suddenly resurfaces in a brutal Tripoli prison, Forrester and Powell risk everything to go under cover as prisoners to break him out; the fly team adjusts to their new and improved HQ.

episodes.name: Magpie
episodes.overview: When an American family's lavish sweet sixteen celebration is cut short after the mother of the birthday girl is found dead near their European estate, the Fly Team heads to Monaco to find the woman's murderer. Vo begins seeing Raines in a new light.

episodes.name: Cowboy Behavior
episodes.overview: The Fly Team heads to Bulgaria in search of a wanted criminal who is exploiting underage American girls. Meanwhile, Raines becomes curious when Forrester asks him to keep an eye on Powell.

episodes.name: Death by Inches
episodes.overview: When a disgraced former U.S. cabinet member is arrested in Vienna, the Fly Team is sent to investigate whether he and his assistant were peddling classified government documents. Powell struggles as he is forced to stay behind on desk duty.

guest_stars.character: Former Secretary of Energy James Gaddis
guest_stars.name: Damian Young

episodes.name: Fire Starter
episodes.overview: The Fly Team is called in to investigate when an American college student is arrested at a hostel in Prague for showing aggression toward local police who were dismissive of her sexual abuse claims. Also, Vo makes use of her sexual assault advocacy experience from her army days as they work to ensure the victim gets justice.

episodes.name: Andiamo!
episodes.overview: The Fly Team heads to the Tuscan countryside after an American couple's son is kidnapped right outside their new home. Concerns are heightened as fingers begin to point to the mafia.

episodes.name: Remove the Compromise
episodes.overview: Assistant Special Agent in Charge Jubal Valentine heads to Budapest to personally help the Fly Team and the CIA take down the cartel that murdered his former girlfriend and colleague. As part of the mission, Forrester poses as an undercover arms expert.

episodes.name: Rules of Blackjack
episodes.overview: When a U.S. mercenary claiming to fight child trafficking abroad is apprehended at a remote Romanian border police outpost after the U.S. DOJ suspects his crew of embezzlement, Tate and Raines attempt to get him to flip on the leader of the group. The mission takes a turn when the outpost is attacked as they work to secure evidence.

episodes.name: Red Light
episodes.overview: When a wild night in Amsterdam for three ex-Navy men ends with one found dead in his hotel room, the Fly Team must dive into the red-light district to hunt down his killer. Meanwhile, Tate finds herself in a bind with her ex over custody of their daughter.

episodes.name: Touts
episodes.overview: When a former member of the Irish Republican Army turned U.S. citizen is shot while in London with his son touring youth football academies, Smitty and the Fly Team work to hunt down the people responsible as the group becomes increasingly violent. While in London, Smitty pays a visit to her mother who she believes can help the team locate an old family friend who may have a connection to the case.

episodes.name: Gift
episodes.overview: When the owner of a prominent cyber security company is murdered in Copenhagen, mass amounts of data are leaked, sending the NSA to the Fly Team for assistance, including the Bureau's liaison to the NSA.

episodes.name: Tuxhorn
episodes.overview: The Fly Team heads to Oslo when they are tipped off that two Norwegian prisoners are being held in Russia.

episodes.name: A Leader, Not a Tourist
episodes.overview: The Fly Team meets Supervisory Special Agent Wesley "Wes" Mitchell when his partner is shot in LA.

episodes.name: The Other Hard Part
episodes.overview: When a U.S. ambassador is taken hostage at a TV station in the Netherlands alongside 70 civilians, the Fly Team is forced to work quickly to find out who they're up against. Meanwhile, Wes works to earn the respect of his new team.

episodes.name: Nothing Sudden About It
episodes.overview: When an American teenager disappears from a beach party during her senior year trip to Portugal, the Fly Team heads up the search, which is further complicated by the missing teen's parents' differing opinions.

episodes.name: The Unwinnable War
episodes.overview: The deputy inspector general calls on Tate, who is fluent in Spanish, to take on her first undercover field mission, joining Wes and the team in Spain as they investigate a seemingly dirty U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration special agent working out of Madrid.
